{"title":"Race Face Adds New 160mm Arm Lengths for Era & Turbine Cranksets","link":"https://bikerumor.com/race-face-160mm-arm-lengths-era-turbine-cranksets/","date":1736961045000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length4-Large-jpeg.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" alt=\"Race Face Era cranks\" /></p>\n<p>Thinking of going shorter with your crankarms? You’re not alone. As mountain bikes and e-mountain bikes have evolved, crank lengths have gotten shorter. Those shorter arms provide better trail clearance to reduce the risk of pedal strike, but can also improve bike fit and potentially reduce knee pain. Some, like Race Face claim that shorter cranks also improve descending performance. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length9-Large-jpeg.webp\"><img width=\"854\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length9-Large-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Race Face Era cranks lengths\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length9-Large-jpeg.webp 854w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length9-Large-200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length9-Large-80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length9-Large-768x1151.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length6-Large-jpeg.webp\"><img width=\"854\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length6-Large-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Race Face Era crank colors\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length6-Large-jpeg.webp 854w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length6-Large-200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length6-Large-80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length6-Large-768x1151.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, Race Face is going shorter for their Era carbon and Turbine aluminum crank arms. Both models gain a 160mm crank arm length option, giving riders the choice of 160, 165, 170, or 175mm lengths. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length1-Large-jpeg.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length1-Large-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Race Face turbine cranks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length1-Large-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length1-Large-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length1-Large-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length1-Large-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length1-Large-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Race-Face-Era-Turbine-160mm-crank-arm-length1-Large-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll find the Turbine cranks priced at $180 and the Era cranks priced at $499, both are sold without chainrings or bottom brackets.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.raceface.com/products/turbine-crankset?variant=41330653102162\" target=\"_blank\"><em>raceface.com</em></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/race-face-160mm-arm-lengths-era-turbine-cranksets/\">Race Face Adds New 160mm Arm Lengths for Era &amp; Turbine Cranksets</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"4e67e8f2df8500c2379cb4576743a93b514e17ba203936ad43718baf847f382e","category":"Cycling"}